column1: Hourly demand profiles for provincial net electricity, end-use space, and end-use water heat demand. Unit: 1/h

Net electricity excluded residential and commercial space and water heating served by electricity. Source: 2016 Telemetred Load from https://www.bchydro.com/energy-in-bc/operations/transmission/transmission-system/balancing-authority-load-data/historical-transmission-data.html

End-use space heat demand is the sum of residential and commercial space heat demand derived from proprietary BC Hydro electricity consumption records from 2016, and National Renewable Energy Laboritory commercial reference building models based on Typified Mean Year climate  conditions in Washington, USA

End-use water heat demand is the sum of residential and commercial space heat demand derived from the Ontario Electric System Operator residential demand profile, and and National Renewable Energy Laboritory commercial reference building models based on Typified Mean Year climate  conditions in Washington, USA
